<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870831-0130 </DOCNO><HL> Texas InstrumentsGets $129.8 MillionOf Navy, Army Jobs</HL><DD> 08/31/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TXN BA GE DRM ROK LTV SMF ML NOC EMR CLG ALDAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Texas Instruments Inc. received contracts totaling $129.8 million for development of an expendable decoy for Navy aircraft and TOW missile equipment for Army armored vehicles.    The Navy contract includes an option for the production of as many as 15,000 decoys.    Units of Boeing Co. received Air Force contracts totaling $63.1 million to support integration of an attack missile into the B1-B aircraft, to modify space-launch rocket upper stages and to modify Minuteman intercontinental ballistic missile training equipment.    Units of General Electric Co. received Navy contracts totaling $41.1 million for propulsion and communications equipment for submarines.    Martin Marietta Corp. received a $33.7 million Air Force contract for Titan space-launch vehicle support services.    LTV Corp. received a $32.9 million Air Force contract for A-7 aircraft improvements.    Hercules Engines Inc. received a $30.7 million Army contract for motor vehicle engines.    Rockwell International Corp. received Air Force contracts totaling $27.9 million for B-1B aircraft test services and spare parts.    Diamond Shamrock Corp.'s Diamond Shamrock Refining andamp; Marketing Co. unit received a $27.1 million defense logistics agency contract for jet fuel.    Units of Singer Co. received contracts totaling $18 million for training equipment for the Navy and helicopter equipment for the Army.    Northrop Corp. received Army contracts totaling $16.6 million for helicopter equipment and missile sensors.    Emerson Electric Co. received a $16.2 million Air Force contract for B-1B aircraft support.    Key Airlines received a $15.2 million Air Force contract for air transportation services.    Arrowhead Products received Air Force contracts totaling $11.6 million for C-141 aircraft equipment.    General Defense Corp., a unit of Clabir Corp., received a $10.7 million Army contract for projectile parts.    Allied-Signal Inc. received a $10 million Navy contract for F-18 aircraft equipment. </TEXT></DOC>